
				                 One person was killed and two others were injured when a taxi and a car collided on the corner of Leslie and Livingstone avenue in Vereeniging on Tuesday, paramedics said.
ER 24 spokesperson Annine Siddall said that at around 6pm paramedics arrived at the scene.
“Unfortunately paramedics could not do anything to save the driver of the taxi and he was declared dead on the scene. A woman, believed to be in her late 20s, sustained moderate injuries and she was transported to Mediclinic Vereeniging for further medical care,” Siddall said.
“One more person sustained minor injuries in the collision.”
She said that the details surrounding the accident was not known and that local authorities were on the scene to investigate.
                         	                  